cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes a superpixel segmentation algorithm that is widely used as a preprocessing step in computer vision works. Additionally, the paper discusses the accuracy and computational efficiency of the proposed algorithm, which are important factors in computer vision research. 

The paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it uses the expectation-maximization method to estimate unknown parameters and assumes that each superpixel corresponds to a Gaussian distribution. 

The graphics (cs.GR) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper discusses the partitioning of an image into perceptually coherence atomic regions, which is related to graphics and image processing. 

Finally, the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category is a possibility as the paper discusses the reduction of the number of entries of subsequent algorithms, which is related to multimedia data processing.
